# Server Actions

## Rules
- File must start with `"use server"`
- Never use `useActionState` — redirect on error instead so forms stay as Server Components
- Always validate FormData with Zod before calling any external service
- Never import from `"zod"` directly — always use `@/lib/validation`

## FormData validation
`formData.get()` returns `File | string | null`. Never cast with `as string`.
Pass raw values to Zod — it handles type checking and produces clean error messages.

```typescript
// ❌ BAD
const email = formData.get("email") as string;

// ✅ GOOD — Zod validates types, presence, and format in one step
const result = loginSchema.safeParse({
  email: formData.get("email"),
  password: formData.get("password"),
});
if (!result.success) {
  redirect(buildFieldErrorUrl("/login", result.error.flatten().fieldErrors));
}
const { email, password } = result.data; // fully typed and safe
```

## Error handling — two levels

Zod field errors → `?{fieldName}Error=` params (shown inline next to each input).
Service/Supabase errors → `?error=` param (shown as a form-level alert).

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD pattern
export async function signIn(formData: FormData) {
  const result = loginSchema.safeParse({ email: formData.get("email"), ... });
  if (!result.success) {
    redirect(buildFieldErrorUrl("/login", result.error.flatten().fieldErrors));
  }
  const { error } = await supabase.auth.signInWithPassword(result.data);
  if (error) redirect(`/login?error=${encodeURIComponent(error.message)}`);
  redirect("/");
}
```

## Surfacing errors in pages and forms
Pages read both sets of params from `searchParams` and pass them as separate props:

```tsx
// page.tsx — reads both levels
const { error, emailError, passwordError } = await searchParams;
return <LoginForm error={error} fieldErrors={{ email: emailError, password: passwordError }} />;

// form component — use <Input> with label/validate/error props (no separate FormField needed)
<Input id="email" name="email" label="Email" validate="email" error={fieldErrors?.email} />
```

## Site URL guard
Never inline `process.env.NEXT_PUBLIC_SITE_URL` — use a guard that throws at startup:

```typescript
function getSiteUrl(): string {
  const url = process.env.NEXT_PUBLIC_SITE_URL;
  if (!url) throw new Error("NEXT_PUBLIC_SITE_URL is not set.");
  return url.replace(/\/$/, "");
}
```
